![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/2a7bf1ef-ab82-421c-9c6c-25cad877d2ed/FB_IMG_1739839895564.jpg?format=original)

This evening's edition of RAW will be emanating from Charlotte, North Carolina at The Spectrum Center. WrestleTix is reporting that 13,410 tickets have been distributed for the event.

In addition to the continuing build towards The Elimination Chamber we have the following matches & appearances advertised:

*   Seth Rollins vs. Finn Balor in an Elimination Chamber qualifying match
    
*   Roxanne Perez vs. Raquel Rodriguez in an Elimination Chamber qualifying match
    
*   A.J. Styles vs. Dominik Mysterio
    
*   Penta vs. Pete Dunne
    
*   Ivy Nile vs. Dakota Kai in a Women’s Intercontinental Championship #1 Contenders match
    
*   Bianca Belair & Naomi will be looking for Liv Morgan & Raquel Rodriguez
    
*   Sami Zayn to appear
    

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/8a71b5a6-fbaf-40bc-8e57-a6515fe92674/Messenger_creation_1153198539331524.jpeg?format=original)

Sami Zayn opens RAW talking about the long stories history between him and Kevin Owens. From the indies to the main event of WrestleMania.

But this time is different. There will be no forgiveness. No forgetting. KO wants to meet in Toronto? Sami Zayn will be there!

Adam Pearce comes out and tells Sami Zayn that this won't be allowed. The WWE can not sanction a match between them.

*   **_AT ELIMINATION CHAMBER! KEVIN OWENS VS SAMI ZAYN IN AN UNSANCTIONED MATCH!!!!!_**
    

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/25f80966-5fd8-48c3-90d4-70c0fa6c6649/Messenger_creation_998564778807170.jpeg?format=original)

